02/03/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- As expected, the cabinet easily survived a no confidence vote Friday (March 2nd), which was filed by the opposition over the government's healthcare policy. 
The three-party ruling coalition was united in its support of the government.
In other news, Sofia hosted the first international forum on security and anti-crime efforts Wednesday evening. 
It drew representatives from state institutions, the business community and NGOs. 
Representatives of security firms from Switzerland, the Netherlands, Poland and Greece shared their experiences. 
(News.bg, bTV, Nova TV - 02/03/07; Novinite - 01/03/07)
